'''[[Madam]] Edgecombe''' was a [[Great Britain|British]] [[Wizardkind|witch]] and the wife of [[Marietta Edgecombe's father|Mr Edgecombe]] and the mother of [[Marietta Edgecombe|Marietta]].<ref name="OOTP18"/><ref name="OOTP27"/>

She worked in the [[British Ministry of Magic]] as a [[Floo Network Regulator]] and assisted [[Dolores Umbridge]] in monitoring the incoming and outgoing communications of the [[Hogwarts Castle]] fireplaces in [[1995]].<ref name="OOTP27">{{OOTP|B|27}}</ref> She was a supporter of the then-Minister [[Cornelius Fudge]]'s claim that [[Tom Riddle|Lord Voldemort]] was dead. Due to her career, she forbade her daughter from doing anything that may get on Umbridge's bad side.<ref name="OOTP18">{{OOTP|B|18}}</ref>

